Population metadata: 1KGphase3

popDat_1KGphase3.Rd

Population metadata: 1KGphase3

popDat_1KGphase3

Format

An object of class data.table (inherits from data.frame) with 2504 rows and 4 columns.

See also

Other LD: LD.1KG_download_vcf(), LD.1KG(), LD.LD_blocks(), LD.UKBiobank(), LD.calculate_LD(), LD.construct_subset_vcf_name(), LD.custom_panel(), LD.dprime_table(), LD.filter_LD(), LD.filter_vcf_gaston(), LD.filter_vcf(), LD.get_locus_vcf_folder(), LD.index_vcf(), LD.leadSNP_block(), LD.load_or_create(), LD.plink_LD(), LD.plink_file(), LD.plot_LD(), LD.query_vcf(), LD.rds_to_npz(), LD.read_bin(), LD.read_ld_table(), LD.run_plink_LD(), LD.save_LD_matrix(), LD.snpstats_get_LD(), LD.snpstats_get_MAF(), LD.translate_population(), LD.vcf_to_bed(), LDlinkR.LDproxy_batch(), popDat_1KGphase1, saveSparse()

Examples

if (FALSE) {
popDat_URL <- "ftp://ftp-trace.ncbi.nih.gov/1000genomes/ftp/release/20130502/integrated_call_samples_v3.20130502.ALL.panel"
popDat_1KGphase3 <-  data.table::fread(text=trimws(gsub(",\t",",",readLines(popDat_URL))), sep="\t",  fill=T, stringsAsFactors = F, col.names = c("sample","population","superpop","sex"), nThread = 4)
usethis::use_data(popDat_1KGphase3, overwrite = T)
}
